# Pomodoro Desktop App

## About

I'm coding a little Pomodoro app because I love the Pomodoro Technique and wanted a desktop version for my personal use. This project is also a great way for me to practice and improve my coding skills.

## What is the Pomodoro Technique?

The Pomodoro Technique is a time management method developed by Francesco Cirillo in the late 1980s. It uses a timer to break work into intervals, traditionally 25 minutes in length, separated by short breaks. This technique helps improve productivity and focus.

## Features

- **Timer:** A simple timer that counts down from 25 minutes (or any custom time you set).
- **Breaks:** Short breaks between work intervals.
- **Customization:** Ability to adjust work and break durations.
- **Notifications:** Desktop notifications to alert you when a work interval or break is over.

## Why This Project?

- **Personal Use:** I wanted a desktop version of a Pomodoro timer that fits my workflow.
- **Learning Opportunity:** This project serves as a training exercise to improve my programming skills, particularly in desktop application development.

## Technologies Used

- **HTML, CSS, JS, Electron

